FeedPackage.Description:
See http://marketplace.sitecore.net/en/Modules/Add_Device_Layout_Wizard.aspx for more information.
When creating a site it's common for many nodes to diverge their layout from their template's Standard Values. Since the layout field encapsulates all devices, once that link is broken it can be a real challenge to add a new device at a later date.
Out-of-the-box the only solution is to construct a new layout on the Standard Values node for the template, determine which nodes no longer use the Standard Values layout, then use the layout Copy Device functionality.
At best this is tedious and error-prone. At worst, completely unworkable.
This module addresses this issue by firstly, identifying all the nodes that are instances of the template but are not using Standard Values. Then applying a new device layout selectively to nodes that don't use the Standard Value, without disturbing the existing layouts.
This component installs to the Sitecore Desktop as a link from the Developer Tools 'Start' menu.
Source is published under the GNU General Public License v3 and is available from http://sitecore.codeplex.com
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: After importing into your Sitecore Web Project you must install the companion Sitecore Package. A folder called _SitecorePackages will be created that will contain the necessary package. This package contains Core database Sitecore Items that connect the application to the Sitecore Shell.
FeedPackage.Summary: Easily roll out a layout for a new device across an existing content tree. Perfect when you decide to add mobile support for your site and you already have hundreds of nodes with configured layout.
FeedPackage.Tags: sitecore module plugin add device layout wizard
FeedPackage.Title: FiveLimes.Sitecore.DeviceLayoutWizard

FeedPackage.Description: The Common Service Locator library contains a shared interface for service location which application and framework developers can reference. The library provides an abstraction over IoC containers and service locators. Using the library allows an application to indirectly access the capabilities without relying on hard references. The hope is that using this library, third-party applications and frameworks can begin to leverage IoC/Service Location without tying themselves down to a specific implementation. This library contains a portable class library that targets .NET Framework 4.5 and .NET Core 1
FeedPackage.Title: CoreCompat.Microsoft.Practices.ServiceLocation
